The paper deals with the computation of geodesic distances on triangular meshes, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and geometric modeling (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of the method for regular sampling and Voronoi tessellation, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm presented in the paper is parallel and involves graph traversal, which are topics related to parallel and distributed computing (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
